nodes.long_description:
Become part of an elite special forces unit and use real-world CQB (Close Quarters Battles) tactics to clear rooms, breach doors, and defeat the enemy threat.

FEATURES:

• Utilize an arsenal of weapons, scopes, sight attachments, explosives and equipment.

• Take note of simulated wind and target distance with the wind meter and spotter scope. Calculate physics-based bullet drop and time-to-hit to improve your accuracy.

• Use stealth to sneak up behind enemies with a silent knife kill. Or go head-to-head against enemies that will take cover and attempt to flank your position.

• Randomized Enemy positions and doors, making each play-through an unknown challenge.

• Non-linear maps give players an endless variety in how they choose to infiltrate and complete missions. Enter buildings through doors, climb ladders to reach rooftops, or climb through windows. The choice is yours.

Tactical Assault VR is currently an Early Access release and is updated regularly.
nodes.short_description: Tactical MilSim CQB (Close Quarters Battles) in Virtual Reality

nodes.change_log:
Tactical Assault VR v0.8.82
• Fixed PvP Kills Scoring

Tactical Assault VR v0.8.81
• Fixed Shootout City dead spectators falling to ground
• Fixed M4 URGI OKP7 reticle misalignment
• Fixed Hidden Forest enemies spawning inside rocks
• Enemy skins based on Mission
• Spawn protection upon revive reduced to 3 seconds
• Room Guard Enemies can now equip a 590 shotgun

• (PCVR) Render to Monitor now disables LCK cameras for creators who prefer external capture tools. Disabling LCK cameras with Render to Monitor ON improves performance for streamers and external capture apps such as OBS. The render preview monitor is disabled as it is tied to the LCK cameras. The Autocycle and camera switch buttons are still active and available for use.
Please Note: The Render Documentary Cameras toggle must be ON for the Render To Monitor option to work

Updates to Ban system:
• TK Decay - A TK penalty is removed every 6 hours.
• Teamkill penalties/banning removed from coop Sandbox and Room Randomizer regardless of the room being public or having AKTK on.
• All Teamkill violations and strikes are reset after a ban is lifted
• AKTK (Autokick Teamkillers) is now OFF by default. Turn it on manually if you prefer a room with stricter penalties
• FF (Friendly Fire) is now OFF by default. Turn it on manually if you prefer a room with stricter penalties
• Team Kills are now assigned to players who down another player after their downed timer runs out. This is a violation and continued abuse will result in a 12-hour ban. The downed player must be revived to prevent the Team Kill violation.

Tactical Assault VR v0.8.8 hotfix (no version change. Non-mandatory but recommended)
• Fixed visual glitches found in VOID
• Fixed visual glitches found in PvP Urban Training map
• Fixed visual glitches found in Shootout Sand

-------------------------------------------------

Tactical Assault VR v0.8.8

Additions:
• Incoming Storm REMASTER
• (Quest) Added LIV Creator Kit (LCK) tools for external camera recording on Stand Alone Meta Quest headsets. Saved videos can be found within the "MOVIES > Tactical AssaultVR Recordings" directory. Use the SideQuest app to access this directory. Or sync media directly to your phone to download through the Meta Horizons app.
• (PCVR) LCK now replaces the previous camera recording method on PCVR. By default, the cameras no longer render on your monitor (as a performance saving measure). You must enable the "Render To Monitor" option for desktop capture. Otherwise, all recording is handled internally through LIV Creator Kit. Saved PCVR recordings will be found in your "Installation Directory > Tactical Assault VR Recordings" directory.
• Added lore/story overview for each mission (written by Canto)
• Added Mission Brief Voice Overs in Singleplayer mission select (Voice overs by Jorin)
• Added TOC Voice Overs for exfil (Voice overs by Jorin)

Griefing/Team Killing:
• Changed: To combat griefing-only lobbies, public rooms are automatically closed if the host has 4+ team kills regardless of the AKTK setting. Private rooms are unaffected by this change
• Changed: To combat griefing-only lobbies, public lobbies are limited to 4 TKs regardless of AKTK. Private rooms are unaffected by this change
• Added 3 strike system to combat griefing. Getting auto-kicked for griefing (constant Team-Killing) gets you a strike. 3 strikes results in a ban from Multiplayer for 12 hours. You will NOT receive a strike if you are vote-kicked or host-kicked from a room. Only if auto-kicked through griefing/team-killing. Strikes do not reset and are accumulated until you are banned.
• Changed: To combat bunny-hopping between public lobbies to grief before being auto-kicked, ALL team-kills are tallied. Reaching the maximum amount of team-kills results in a 12-hour ban.

Changes/Updates:
• Improved Bullet Penetration
• Updated Enemy logic with performance optimizations
• Weapons are automatically charged if the AutoSling option is ON. Excludes shotguns and LMGs
• Updated Hidden Forest

• Updated Shootout Sand respawn points away from middle of the map
• Reduced AKTK limit to 2 TKs until kicked.

Fixes:
• Fixed Beanbag shotgun damaging player. Beanbag shotguns no longer damage players but still cause screen blackout
• Fixed PvP private rooms no longer count Team Kills with AKTK off

PCVR Exclusives:
• Added Realtime Shadows option in Graphics settings
